medical_history.chief_complaint: The patient presented with 4 months of vaginal discharge.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 4 months prior to presentation, characterized by watery vaginal discharge. The examination revealed cervical thickening with a diameter of approximately 4.5 cm and positive blood on palpation.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient had been in menopause for 9 years.
